There is a lot of ways to solve this.

My approach is based on the selection specificity.

The css that handles your active is:

    .nav-pills&gt;li.active&gt;a

And you used:

    #myScrollspy a:visited

The selector you used has a better specificity than the other because it has an `id`. You should try to keep the same level of specificity, if not you will override this values.

Solution:

    .nav-pills&gt;li&gt;a:visited  {
        color: inherit;
