So I made this side bar linking to sections on the same page with bootstrap:
[![enter image description here][1]][1]


However, as you can see, when I click on a section, the link will be marked as visited and thus get the typical blue color.
I know I can undo this with  

    .a:visited {
                    color:inherit;
                }

However, the active section, also will have the black color.
[![enter image description here][2]][2]

So my question basically is either:

1. How can I remove the blue color of the visited &quot;link&quot; without it messing with the color the active section.

or

2. How can I change the color of the active section (from black to white)?


